nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Alanine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: L-Alanine is synthesized through a convergent prebiotic network originating from CO\u2082, H\u2082, NH\u2083, and HCN. Four major hub molecules \u2014 pyruvate, acetaldehyde, formate, and HCN \u2014 channel carbon and nitrogen from hydrothermal vent chemistry (CO\u2082 reduction on iron-sulfur minerals, Fischer-Tropsch-type synthesis) into surface chemistry (Strecker synthesis, wet-dry dehydration) and biochemical assembly (transamination, reductive amination). Ten distinct pathways connect simple C1 gases to L-alanine via reductive amination of pyruvate, Strecker synthesis through acetaldehyde, transamination with glycine, and amination of lactate. The network emphasizes redundancy: pyruvate itself is accessible from at least three independent hydrothermal routes, and the Strecker branch operates independently on the surface using HCN derived from multiple sources.\n\nMOLECULES (17 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen gas) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CO (carbon monoxide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: CHOO- (formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H6N2 (2-aminopropionitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H7NO2 (L-Alanine) [target]\n  - mol_013: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C3H6O3 (lactic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C2H2O3 (glyoxylic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_017: C2H4N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (17 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_008 (CO\u2082 hydrogenation to formate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006, mol_004 (Reverse water-gas shift reaction on magnetite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_006, mol_002 -> mol_007 (Fischer-Tropsch-type synthesis of formaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_008, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_010, mol_004 (Stepwise CO\u2082 fixation to pyruvate via formate on greigite) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_006, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_010, mol_004 (Acetyl-CoA pathway analog: CO/CO\u2082 to pyruvate on FeNiS) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_012, mol_004 (Reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_007: mol_010 -> mol_009, mol_001 (Thermal decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_008: mol_006, mol_002 -> mol_009 (Fischer-Tropsch-type synthesis of acetaldehyde from CO) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_009: mol_009, mol_003, mol_005 -> mol_011, mol_004 (Strecker synthesis step 1: aminonitrile formation from acetaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_011, mol_004 -> mol_012, mol_003 (Strecker synthesis step 2: hydrolysis of aminonitrile to alanine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_007, mol_003, mol_005 -> mol_017, mol_004 (Strecker synthesis of aminoacetonitrile (glycine precursor)) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_017, mol_004 -> mol_013, mol_003 (Hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_013: mol_010, mol_013 -> mol_012, mol_016 (Transamination of pyruvate by glycine to form alanine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_014: mol_008, mol_003 -> mol_014, mol_004 (Condensation of formate and ammonia to formamide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_015: mol_014 -> mol_005, mol_004 (UV photolysis of formamide to HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_016: mol_010, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Reduction of pyruvate to lactate on FeS) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_017: mol_015, mol_003 -> mol_012, mol_004 (Amination of lactate to alanine) [Surface]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal formate-pyruvate reductive amination (3 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal acetyl-CoA analog pathway to alanine (3 steps)\n  - P3: Fischer-Tropsch acetaldehyde to alanine via Strecker (4 steps)\n  - P4: Pyruvate decarboxylation to acetaldehyde + Strecker (5 steps)\n  - P5: CO-route pyruvate decarboxylation + Strecker (5 steps)\n  - P6: Formate-pyruvate-lactate-amination pathway (4 steps)\n  - P7: CO-route pyruvate-lactate-amination pathway (4 steps)\n  - P8: Transamination: glycine donates amino group to pyruvate (7 steps)\n  - P9: Formamide-HCN-Strecker pathway via FTT acetaldehyde (7 steps)\n  - P10: Formamide-HCN + FTT formaldehyde \u2192 glycine \u2192 transamination (9 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_010, mol_009, mol_005, mol_008\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 4\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.90, \"rxn_004\": 0.65, \"rxn_006\": 0.70},\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.72,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.75,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.60,\n      \"targe